<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Certificate Comparison</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <style>
    .container {
      max-width: 1000px;
      margin: 50px auto;
      padding: 20px;
      background-color: #fff;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
    }
    
    h1, h2 {
      color: #333;
      text-align: center;
    }
    
    .comparison {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      justify-content: space-around;
      margin-top: 30px;
    }
    
    .certificate-option {
      width: 45%;
      min-width: 300px;
      margin-bottom: 30px;
      padding: 20px;
      border: 1px solid #ddd;
      border-radius: 5px;
      background-color: #f9f9f9;
    }
    
    .option-title {
      font-size: 20px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      color: #333;
      text-align: center;
    }
    
    .pros-cons {
      margin-top: 20px;
    }
    
    .pros, .cons {
      margin-bottom: 15px;
    }
    
    .pros h3, .cons h3 {
      color: #333;
      font-size: 16px;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }
    
    .pros ul {
      color: #4CAF50;
    }
    
    .cons ul {
      color: #f44336;
    }
    
    .pros li, .cons li {
      margin-bottom: 5px;
      color: #333;
    }
    
    .pros h3:before {
      content: "✓ ";
      color: #4CAF50;
    }
    
    .cons h3:before {
      content: "✗ ";
      color: #f44336;
    }
    
    .btn {
      display: block;
      width: 200px;
      margin: 20px auto;
      padding: 10px;
      background-color: #4CAF50;
      color: white;
      text-align: center;
      text-decoration: none;
      border-radius: 5px;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    
    .btn:hover {
      background-color: #45a049;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('../partials/navbar') %>
  
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Certificate Generation Comparison</h1>
    <p style="text-align: center;">Compare the two different methods of generating certificates</p>
    
    <div class="comparison">
      <div class="certificate-option">
        <div class="option-title">HTML-Based Certificate</div>
        <p>This method uses an HTML template that is converted to PDF.</p>
        
        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros">
            <h3>Advantages</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Easier to style using CSS</li>
              <li>More flexible layout options</li>
              <li>Can use web fonts and HTML elements</li>
              <li>Easier to make responsive</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="cons">
            <h3>Disadvantages</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>May have inconsistent rendering across devices</li>
              <li>Can have overflow issues with text</li>
              <li>PDF conversion may not be pixel-perfect</li>
              <li>More complex to debug layout issues</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <a href="/student/certificate/test-html" class="btn">Download Example</a>
      </div>
      
      <div class="certificate-option">
        <div class="option-title">PNG-Based Certificate</div>
        <p>This method uses Canvas to create a PNG image that is converted to PDF.</p>
        
        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros">
            <h3>Advantages</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Pixel-perfect control over layout</li>
              <li>Consistent rendering across all devices</li>
              <li>No text overflow issues</li>
              <li>Better for complex designs with graphics</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          
          <div class="cons">
            <h3>Disadvantages</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>More code required for styling</li>
              <li>Less flexible for responsive designs</li>
              <li>Font loading can be more complex</li>
              <li>May require more manual positioning</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <a href="/student/certificate/test-png" class="btn">Download Example</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Recommendation</h2>
    <p style="text-align: center;">For certificates with fixed dimensions and precise layout requirements, the <strong>PNG-based approach</strong> is recommended as it provides more consistent results across all devices and prevents text overflow issues.</p>
  </div>
  
  <%- include('../partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>
